data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
Former President Obama, speaking tonight at the DNC, presented Vice President Kamala Harris as a change agent and fighter for progressive causes and a more hopeful politics.

Los Angeles has agreed to spend at least $20.8 million on improvements to the Hyperion sewage plant after a massive spill of untreated wastewater in 2021.

The Girl Scouts in this troop, in one of New York’s emergency migrant shelters, know hardship and loss. But at meetings at least, they get to be kids.

A new assessment of U.S. weather alerts underlines the growing risks the country faces as climate change continues to intensify extremes.

Continuing to support ‘Espinas,’ her musica Mexicana album, the Inglewood-born singer reveals a new fall tour across the country.

Justin Turner will always be a Dodger, and the ovations he received in his first game back at Dodger Stadium show why he deserves one more season in L.A.
